   298	### G. Build & CI config
   299	
   300	**Bootstrap is docs-only**, so CI runs exactly one check.
   301	
   302	- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — single workflow named `ci`, single job
   303	  named **`docs-lint`**. That job name is also the required status
   304	  check in branch protection (pinned explicitly so the `gh api` call
   305	  is deterministic).
   306	- The `docs-lint` job:
   307	  1. Checks out.
   308	  2. Runs `markdownlint-cli2 "**/*.md" "#node_modules" "#.venv"` (or
   309	     pinned-version equivalent). Configuration comes from the repo's
   310	     `.markdownlint.json`.
   311	  3. Exits 0 if all markdown passes.
   312	- **No Python job** at bootstrap (no Python files exist).
   313	- **No JSON Schema job** at bootstrap (no schemas exist, and an
   314	  empty-glob job is brittle — either a find returning nothing exits 0
   315	  quietly and hides a real misconfiguration, or the tool errors on
   316	  no-input. Easier to add this job in Phase 1 when the first schema
   317	  lands.)
   318	- **Later phases add jobs**, each as a distinct job name (so branch
   319	  protection can require each one as it stabilizes):
   320	  - Phase 1: `schema-validity` — validates `spec/v0/schemas/*.schema.json`.
   321	  - Phase 3: `python-lint` (ruff), `python-typecheck` (pyright),
   322	    `python-test` (pytest) — once the first package exists and has a
   323	    real test.
   324	  - Phase 3+: `schema-parity` — Pydantic models match their JSON
   325	    Schemas.
   326	  - Phase 11: `conformance` — runs the conformance suite against
   327	    the reference impl.
   328	
   329	### H. Git + GitHub execution
   330	
   331	Same as before:
   332	
   333	1. `git init -b main`
   334	2. Initial commit containing all of the above.
   335	3. `gh auth status`.
   336	4. `gh repo create eden --private --source . --remote origin --push \
   337	   --description "A protocol for directed code evolution orchestration"`.
   338	5. `gh repo edit --add-topic protocol --add-topic specification \
   339	   --add-topic directed-evolution --add-topic orchestration \
   340	   --add-topic ai --add-topic research-automation`.
   341	6. Wait for the first `docs-lint` run on `main` to complete (so the
   342	   check name is registered in GitHub's status-check cache), **then**
   343	   enable branch protection.
   344	7. Branch protection uses **classic branch protection** (not the
   345	   newer repository rulesets — classic is better-documented for
   346	   scripted setup and the two tools can coexist). Call:
   347	
   348	   ```bash
   349	   gh api -X PUT "repos/<user>/eden/branches/main/protection" \
   350	     -H "Accept: application/vnd.github+json" \
   351	     --input - <<'JSON'
   352	   {
   353	     "required_status_checks": {
   354	       "strict": true,
   355	       "contexts": ["docs-lint"]
   356	     },
   357	     "enforce_admins": false,
   358	     "required_pull_request_reviews": {
   359	       "required_approving_review_count": 0,
   360	       "dismiss_stale_reviews": false,
   361	       "require_code_owner_reviews": false
   362	     },
   363	     "restrictions": null,
   364	     "allow_force_pushes": false,
   365	     "allow_deletions": false
   366	   }
   367	   JSON
   368	   ```
   369	
   370	   Rationale for each field:
   371	   - `contexts: ["docs-lint"]` — exact CI job name pinned in section G.
   372	     Added to as Phase 3 / Phase 11 introduce more jobs.
   373	   - `enforce_admins: false` — solo-repo hotfix path stays open.
   374	   - `required_approving_review_count: 0` — solo contributor;
   375	     bumping this to 1+ would block every merge. Increase when
   376	     collaborators arrive.
   377	   - `strict: true` — branches must be up-to-date with `main` before
   378	     merging; cheap safety on a low-traffic repo.
   379	   - `allow_force_pushes: false`, `allow_deletions: false` — keep
   380	     `main` durable.
